{"type": "qna", "question": {"id": "850830038420422656", "type": 19, "content": "Sea of Thieves have a System for Music which is great. Sure there are 'pre scripted' Events. But the Server-Client communication is well so that when people join they just add another line of music to the already played Track. So its not 'that hard'. Only if you would make it completly played by the players itself.", "channel_id": "829113775876735026", "author": {"id": "232502850712895488", "username": "Kael", "avatar": "49b6a2444c4b7b71ef85d95f6bbca359", "discriminator": "3570", "public_flags": 0}, "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "mentions": [{"id": "733088119280369757", "username": "S6Sheevok", "avatar": null, "discriminator": "7073", "public_flags": 0}], "mention_roles": [], "pinned": false, "mention_everyone": false, "tts": false, "timestamp": "2021-06-05T20:14:48.817000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "flags": 0, "components": [], "message_reference": {"channel_id": "829113775876735026", "guild_id": "809856101326913567", "message_id": "850829544150794260"}, "referenced_message": {"id": "850829544150794260", "type": 19, "content": "No, it's really about the timing. People are very, very sensitive to the timing of musical notes. If your ping is 80 ms and someone else's ping is 80 ms, it could be 160 ms for the note you hit to *start* playing. So if you're both trying to time everything together, there's actual a 160+ ms delay *both ways*.", "channel_id": "829113775876735026", "author": {"id": "733088119280369757", "username": "S6Sheevok", "avatar": null, "discriminator": "7073", "public_flags": 0}, "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "mentions": [{"id": "232222080823853056", "username": "Invis", "avatar": "3566ba27c0c29058f4330b9c962b9976", "discriminator": "5618", "public_flags": 0}], "mention_roles": [], "pinned": false, "mention_everyone": false, "tts": false, "timestamp": "2021-06-05T20:12:50.974000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "flags": 0, "components": [], "message_reference": {"channel_id": "829113775876735026", "guild_id": "809856101326913567", "message_id": "850828919707795538"}}}, "answer": {"id": "850830295992500265", "type": 19, "content": "Right. It's not impossble or unfeasible. But it is not as simple as letting people press a key to make a sound. No one would be happy with that version of it.", "channel_id": "829113775876735026", "author": {"id": "733088119280369757", "username": "S6Sheevok", "avatar": null, "discriminator": "7073", "public_flags": 0}, "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "mentions": [{"id": "232502850712895488", "username": "Kael", "avatar": "49b6a2444c4b7b71ef85d95f6bbca359", "discriminator": "3570", "public_flags": 0}], "mention_roles": [], "pinned": false, "mention_everyone": false, "tts": false, "timestamp": "2021-06-05T20:15:50.227000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "flags": 0, "components": [], "message_reference": {"channel_id": "829113775876735026", "guild_id": "809856101326913567", "message_id": "850830038420422656"}, "hit": true}}